com.jnape.palatable.lambda.lens

Interface LensLike<S,T,A,B,LL extends LensLike>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the "larger" value for reading
    T - the type of the "larger" value for putting
    A - the type of the "smaller" value that is read
    B - the type of the "smaller" update value
    LL - the concrete lens subtype
    All Superinterfaces:
    Applicative<T,LensLike<S,?,A,B,LL>>, Contravariant<S,Profunctor<?,T,LensLike<?,?,A,B,LL>>>, Functor<T,LensLike<S,?,A,B,LL>>, Monad<T,LensLike<S,?,A,B,LL>>, Profunctor<S,T,LensLike<?,?,A,B,LL>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Iso<S,T,A,B>, Iso.Simple<S,A>, Lens<S,T,A,B>, Lens.Simple<S,A>, LensLike.Simple<S,A,LL>, Schema<Values>, TypeSafeKey<A,B>, TypeSafeKey.Simple<A>

    public interface LensLike<S,T,A,B,LL extends LensLike>
extends Monad<T,LensLike<S,?,A,B,LL>>, Profunctor<S,T,LensLike<?,?,A,B,LL>>
    The generic supertype of all types that can be treated as lenses but should preserve type-specific return types in overrides. This type only exists to appease Java's unfortunate parametric type hierarchy constraints. If you're here, you're probably looking for Lens or Iso.
    See Also:
    Lens, Iso
